# Code Organization

## Default scaffold (`Assets/Game/`)

```
Assets/Game/
├── Art/
│   ├── Materials/         # URP Lit (level backdrop, props)
│   ├── VFX/               # .vfx graphs (strict VFX Graph policy)
│   └── …                  (Animations, Models, Textures)
├── Audio/        (Music, SFX)
├── Prefabs/
│   ├── Cameras/           # Cinemachine rigs
│   └── Effects/           # VisualEffect prefabs
├── UI/
│   └── Runtime/           (Controllers, Views, UXML, USS — Game.UI.asmdef)
├── Settings/
│   ├── Input/             # GameInputActions.inputactions
│   ├── UI/                # PanelSettings
│   ├── Rendering/         # RPAsset.asset, Renderer.asset, DefaultVolumeProfile
│   └── ProjectBootstrap/
├── Scenes/
│   ├── Bootstrap.unity    # persistent systems, build index 0
│   ├── MainMenu.unity     # main menu scene, build index 1
│   ├── Game.unity         # gameplay scene, build index 2
│   ├── Levels/
│   └── Menus/
├── Scripts/
│   ├── Runtime/
│   │   ├── Core/          # Game.Core — GameManager, GameSession, GameAudio, BootstrapSceneLoader
│   │   ├── Input/         # Game.Input.asmdef (generated actions class)
│   │   ├── Gameplay/      # Game.Gameplay.asmdef
│   │   └── Utilities/
│   ├── Editor/
│   └── Tests/
```

Add subfolders (`ScriptableObjects/`, `Prefabs/Characters/`, …) when the project needs them — not required in the empty template.

## Assemblies (functional names)

| Assembly | Namespace | Folder |
|----------|-----------|--------|
| `Game.Core` | `Game.Core` | `Scripts/Runtime/Core/` |
| `Game.Input` | `Game.Input` | `Scripts/Runtime/Input/` (generated from Settings/Input/) |
| `Game.UI` | `Game.UI` | `UI/Runtime/` |
| `Game.Gameplay` | `Game.Gameplay` | `Scripts/Runtime/Gameplay/` (refs `Game.Core`, `Game.Input`, `Unity.Cinemachine`, `Unity.VisualEffectGraph.Runtime`) |
| `Game.Editor` | `Game.Editor` | `Scripts/Editor/` |
| `Game.Tests` | `Game.Tests` | `Scripts/Tests/` |

Add new asmdefs when you need a hard boundary beyond the defaults above.

## Assets & scenes

- **PascalCase** asset names; organize by folders, not prefixes (`Prefabs/Characters/PlayerKnight.prefab`)
- Scenes: `Level01_Forest.unity`, `MenuMain.unity`, `TestPlayerMovement.unity`

## Scene hierarchy

```
--- SYSTEMS ---     # DontDestroyOnLoad (GameManager, AudioManager, …)
--- CAMERAS ---     # Main Camera + CinemachineBrain, CinemachineCamera(s)
--- LEVEL ---       # Environment, lighting, GameplayReveal, greybox
--- UI ---          # UIDocument / UI Toolkit (e.g. MainMenu on MainMenu.unity)
--- DYNAMIC ---     # runtime spawned
```

## Prefabs

Group by role: `Model`, `Colliders`, `Effects`, `Audio` — not one flat list of components.

## Practices

- Runtime vs Editor code in separate asmdefs
- ScriptableObjects + EventChannel pattern when shared config/events grow
- Separate concerns: Core, Gameplay, UI (`Assets/Game/UI/`), Utilities
- Tests in `Game.Tests` with references to runtime asmdefs

## Third-party packages

```
Packages/manifest.json              # UniTask, URP, Cinemachine, VFX Graph, feature packs — no com.unity.ugui
Assets/Plugins/UniRx/               # Vendored UniRx (trimmed — see TRIM_NOTES.md)
Assets/Plugins/Roslyn/            # MCP execute_code C# 12+ (see ROSlyn_NOTES.md)
Assets/Game/UI/Runtime/Extensions/  # UI Toolkit bridge for UniRx + UniTask
```

### Feature packs (manifest)

| Package | Brings |
|---------|--------|
| `com.unity.feature.characters-animation` | Animation Rigging, Timeline, Cinemachine |

Direct pins: `com.unity.cinemachine`, `com.coplaydev.unity-mcp`.

Cameras: `unity-cinemachine.mdc`.

After updating UniRx from Asset Store, re-apply trim per `Assets/Plugins/UniRx/TRIM_NOTES.md`.

## Cursor bootstrap

Project rules live in `.cursor/` at the repository root. `.cursorrules` controls commit message language. Unity Editor opens Cursor once per session and keeps MCP stdio configured via `Assets/Game/Scripts/Editor/Mcp/`.
